raw_attributes.message: mf adjuster is a font with a very basic form, plain architectural, highly functional, almost crystalline. it follows a strict grid and a simple no-curves-policy and comes along with a rather reduced set of parameters. although the dimension and proportion of mf adjuster (http://metaflop.com/modulator?fontface=Adjuster) can vary, its sophistication derives from the pen parameter: you can choose from circle, square or razor.

raw_attributes.message: mf bespoke is geared to contemporary and simply constructed sans serif fonts. the geometrical construction is based on a rectangle and can easily be transformed by means of the parameters increase and superness to an octagon. the parameter superness generates in its lower values unusual and playful results of curves. mf bespoke (http://metaflop.com/modulator?fontface=Bespoke) consists of adjustable parameters grouped in classes of dimension, proportion and shape. this wide range enables you to create sans serif fonts for a broad variety of use. for a classic and elegant version just add a bit of contrast to the default settings.

raw_attributes.message:
projects showcase

although the modulator will always be enriched with new metafonts, we want this platform to be used mainly for exchange, for exploring and generating fresh and playful ideas.
we encourage designers and artists who would like to experiment and make projects not only with us, but also on their own. send us your proposals you made using our fonts. there will be a selection after which the best ones will be published on the projects section.
we are proud to present the first metaflop related work: lovehate (http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.474853655862031.123140.474285165918880&type=1) by the swiss artist christian vetter (http://www.christianvetter.ch/).
raw_attributes.name: project: lovehate
raw_attributes.description: all the works of christian vetter (http://www.christianvetter.ch) gravitate around the topic of painting and generating new possibilities of perception: how can a work stay as an ornament, completely abstract, and in the same time produce a meaning, a content? christian vetter uses mf adjuster (http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.474860992527964.123142.474285165918880&type=1) as a structure, as a construction kit in order to build autonomous in-between spaces. this time, as an exception in his work, the meaning of the words is not secondary, but the main focus stays on the affiliation of the font to image. the phrase structure stays, one word or one letter changes which creates not only a different space disposition but simultaneously a new meaning.

raw_attributes.message:
hello world

welcome to metaflop! although it's still beta and going through heavy development, you can already generate your own metafonts with the modulator (http://metaflop.com/modulator), export them as otf, and take them home with you for free. check our fonts mf adjuster and mf bespoke and spread the word! for more infos, see our terms (http://metaflop.com/terms) and faq (http://metaflop.com/faq).
this is an open source project and you are encouraged to contribute to it: you can find our source code on github (https://github.com/greyfont), both for the source code of the webpage and for all the fonts.
